'''Asuka-Fujiwara: Archaeological sites of Japan’s Ancient Capitals and Related Properties''' is a cluster of archaeological sites from in and around the late sixth- to early eighth-century [[Capital of Japan|capitals]] of [[Asuka, Yamato|Asuka]] and [[Fujiwara-kyō]], [[Nara Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. In 2007, twenty eight sites were submitted jointly for future inscription on the [[UNESCO]] [[World Heritage List]] under the [[World Heritage Site#Cultural criteria|ii, iii, iv, v, and vi]] criteria. Currently, the submission is listed on the [[World Heritage Site#Nominating process|Tentative List]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://whc.unesco.org/en/tentativelists/5097/ |title=Asuka-Fujiwara: Archaeological sites of Japan’s Ancient Capitals and Related Properties |publisher=[[UNESCO]] |accessdate=14 May 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.asukamura.jp/sekaiisan/intro.html |title=Monuments |publisher=[[Asuka, Nara|Asuka Mura]] |accessdate=2 Feb 2013}}</ref>

Since 2011, the Cultural Landscape of the Asuka Hinterland has been [[Cultural Properties of Japan|protected]] as one of the [[Cultural Landscapes of Japan]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/bsys/maindetails.asp?register_id=412&item_id=00003735 |title=奥飛鳥の文化的景観 |trans-title=Cultural Landscape of the Asuka Hinterland |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=12 June 2012}}</ref> An area of 60 ha is also [[National Government Parks|protected]] within the [[Asuka Historical National Government Park]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.asuka-park.go.jp/asuka_en/index.html |title=Asuka Historical National Government Park |publisher=[[Asuka Historical National Government Park]] |accessdate=12 June 2012}}</ref> Related artefacts are housed at the [[Asuka Historical Museum]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nabunken.go.jp/english/asuka.html |title=Asuka Historical Museum |publisher=[[Nara National Research Institute for Cultural Properties]] |accessdate=12 June 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121211021525/http://www.nabunken.go.jp/english/asuka.html |archivedate=11 December 2012 }}</ref>

